South Africans may be on lockdown but this will not stop them from having fun and dressing up, even if it means using their pillows as high-end couture. Celebrities and the public have been flocking to Twitter since the weekend to share snaps of their runway-worthy pillow outfits, accessorised with clutches, handbags and yes, cute sunnies. Some of these looks are so good, we might see them at high-end fashion events post the coronavirus shutdown. Here are 10 people who killed the pillow challenge, from actress Linda Mtoba to former Miss SA, Liesl Laurie: